Jan 7 2009 	Great little hotel	I stayed for two nights in October 08 with my wife and four children. Found the reception and concierge to be very friendly and helpful to my family. Of the 6 of us only my wife could hear the disco when we were on the 3rd floor. They moved us to a higher floor away from the discos without any problem next day. Other staff in restaurant were friendly also. Looks as though a lot of Russians stay here and so some of the staff are Russian speakers only.The free shuttles to airport, beach and markets are great especially for a large family. The hotel was good value compared with others we looked at in Dubai. Depending on why you are visiting the hotel is in a good spot for sight-seeing and shops. If you want to go to the beach every day you are probably better going to a new resort area as Deira can get clogged up with traffic and it may take a while to get there.There are no fridges in rooms but there is a shop across the road to buy cool drinks and snacks. The hotel has 2 lifts, not one. The decor is old but I found it refreshing, sort of old European with thick wooden doors, plush carpet and low lighting, rather than the sterile chain hotel decor where every room looks the same. The rooms are clean and quiet and if you get a room on the corner of a floor they are a lot bigger.The most lasting memory are the friendly staff. If you decide to stay here and have any problem make sure you talk to Yusuf the concierge, he will help you out.	
